07/01/2008
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- President Tassos Papadopoulos on Friday (January 4th) called for the resumption of talks aimed at finding a peaceful settlement to the Cypriot issue. "In our contacts with our Turkish Cypriot compatriots and UN representatives, we insisted on the urgent initiation of talks," Papadopoulos told foreign correspondents in Nicosia. "I think we are now in a stronger position to pursue a solution to the Cyprus problem, which the people of Cyprus deserve," Papadopoulos said, reiterating his commitment to a bi-zonal, bi-communal federation. (RIA Novosti, CNA - 04/01/08)
